# Accessibility Patterns

## Semantic HTML
- **Use proper HTML elements** - buttons, headings, lists, forms
- **ARIA labels** - Add descriptive labels for screen readers
- **Role attributes** - Define component roles when needed
- **Landmark elements** - Use main, nav, section, article

## Keyboard Navigation
- **Tab order** - Ensure logical tab sequence
- **Focus management** - Handle focus in modals and dynamic content
- **Keyboard shortcuts** - Provide keyboard alternatives
- **Focus indicators** - Visible focus states

## Screen Reader Support
- **Alt text** - Descriptive alt text for images
- **Live regions** - Announce dynamic content changes
- **Headings hierarchy** - Proper h1-h6 structure
- **Form labels** - Associate labels with form controls

## Color and Contrast
- **Color contrast** - Meet WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 ratio)
- **Color independence** - Don't rely solely on color for meaning
- **High contrast mode** - Support system high contrast
- **Focus indicators** - Visible focus states

## Mobile Accessibility
- **Touch targets** - Minimum 44px touch targets
- **Gesture alternatives** - Provide button alternatives to gestures
- **Orientation support** - Support both portrait and landscape
- **Zoom support** - Support up to 200% zoom

## Testing Accessibility
- **Automated testing** - Use axe-core and similar tools
- **Manual testing** - Test with screen readers and keyboard
- **User testing** - Include users with disabilities
- **Regular audits** - Check accessibility regularly

## React Native Specific
- **Accessibility props** - Use accessibilityLabel, accessibilityHint
- **Screen reader** - Test with TalkBack (Android) and VoiceOver (iOS)
- **Semantic elements** - Use proper React Native components
- **Focus management** - Handle focus in navigation